<task id="AIPU2-022" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build CitationVerificationService with IVerificationProvider Interface</title>
    <phase>2B</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, ai-safety, citations</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-006</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    Build the CitationVerificationService and its IVerificationProvider abstraction. The service extracts
    legal citations from AI-generated text using regex patterns, classifies each citation by type (case law,
    statute, patent, SEC filing, regulation), and routes it to the appropriate provider for verification.
    This is the backbone of FR-403 (citation verification as a multi-provider capability). The interface
    must be extensible so new providers (CourtListener, USPTO, EDGAR, eCFR, etc.) can be registered without
    changing the core service.
  </prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET backend engineer with knowledge of legal citation formats and Spaarke AI tool patterns.</role>
  <goal>
    CitationVerificationService correctly extracts and type-classifies citations from LLM output text using
    regex, and routes each to its registered IVerificationProvider. Provider routing is fully covered by tests.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/ai.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r2/spec.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read spec.md section FR-403 for the full citation verification requirements and provider list.</step>
    <step>Create CitationType.cs enum: CaseLaw, Statute, Patent, SecFiling, Regulation, Unknown.</step>
    <step>Create Citation.cs record: RawText (string), CitationType (CitationType), NormalizedKey (string — canonical identifier, e.g. "410 U.S. 113" or "35 U.S.C. § 101").</step>
    <step>Create CitationVerificationResult.cs record: Citation (Citation), IsVerified (bool), ConfidenceScore (float 0-1), SourceUrl (string?), VerifiedText (string?), VerificationProvider (string), LatencyMs (double).</step>
    <step>Create IVerificationProvider.cs interface with: string ProviderName { get; }, IReadOnlyList&lt;CitationType&gt; SupportedTypes { get; }, Task&lt;CitationVerificationResult&gt; VerifyAsync(Citation citation, CancellationToken ct), Task&lt;IReadOnlyList&lt;Citation&gt;&gt; SearchAsync(string query, CancellationToken ct), Task&lt;string?&gt; GetFullTextAsync(Citation citation, CancellationToken ct).</step>
    <step>Create ICitationVerificationService.cs interface with: Task&lt;IReadOnlyList&lt;Citation&gt;&gt; ExtractAsync(string text), Task&lt;IReadOnlyList&lt;CitationVerificationResult&gt;&gt; VerifyAllAsync(string text, CancellationToken ct).</step>
    <step>Create CitationExtractor.cs with regex patterns for each CitationType: case law (e.g. \d+ [A-Z]\.\w+\.?\w*\.? \d+), statute (e.g. \d+ U\.S\.C\.?\s+§\s+\d+), patent (e.g. U\.S\. Patent No\.?\s+[\d,]+), SEC (e.g. \d+-[A-Z]), regulation (e.g. \d+ C\.F\.R\.?\s+§\s+\d+). Extract, normalize, and classify each match.</step>
    <step>Create CitationVerificationService.cs implementing ICitationVerificationService. Inject IEnumerable&lt;IVerificationProvider&gt; (all registered providers). In VerifyAllAsync: extract citations, for each citation find the first registered provider that supports its type, call VerifyAsync, collect results. Unknown citations → CitationVerificationResult with IsVerified=false, VerificationProvider="none".</step>
    <step>Register ICitationVerificationService (singleton) and all IVerificationProvider implementations in AddAiSafetyModule().</step>
    <step>Write unit tests for CitationExtractor: each regex pattern matches expected citations, does not match noise. Write unit tests for CitationVerificationService: correct provider selected per type, unknown type returns unverified result, provider exception handled gracefully.</step>
    <step>Run `dotnet build` and `dotnet test --filter "Citation"` to verify.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>CitationExtractor regex correctly identifies all five citation types in test strings.</criterion>
    <criterion>CitationExtractor normalizes raw text to a canonical NormalizedKey for each type.</criterion>
    <criterion>IVerificationProvider interface supports all three operations: VerifyAsync, SearchAsync, GetFullTextAsync.</criterion>
    <criterion>CitationVerificationService routes each citation to the first provider supporting its CitationType.</criterion>
    <criterion>Citations with no supporting provider return IsVerified=false (not an exception).</criterion>
    <criterion>Provider exceptions are caught per-citation and result in IsVerified=false with error noted.</criterion>
    <criterion>Unit tests pass: `dotnet test --filter "Citation"`.</criterion>
    <criterion>Build succeeds with no new warnings.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
